\DOC mk_disj

\TYPE {mk_disj : term * term -> term}

\SYNOPSIS
Constructs a disjunction.

\DESCRIBE
If {t1} and {t2} are terms, both of type {bool}, then 
{mk_disj(t1,t2)} returns the term {t1 \/ t2}.

\FAILURE
Fails if both of {t1} and {t2} have type {bool}.

\SEEALSO
dest_disj, is_disj, list_mk_disj, strip_disj.

\ENDDOC
